.TH "input_set_capability" 9 "input_set_capability" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
input_set_capability \- mark device as capable of a certain event
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" input_set_capability
.BI "(struct input_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int type "  ","
.BI "unsigned int code "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device that is capable of emitting or accepting event
.IP "type" 12
type of the event (EV_KEY, EV_REL, etc...)
.IP "code" 12
event code
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
In addition to setting up corresponding bit in appropriate capability
bitmap the function also adjusts dev->evbit.
